SIMPLE: warty
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Warty
<hw>Wart"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having
warts; full of warts; overgrow with warts; <as>as, a <ex>warty</ex>
leaf</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Of the nature of warts; <as>as, a <ex>warty</ex>
excrescence</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Warty egg</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>a marine
univalve shell (<spn>Ovulum verrucosum</spn>), having the surface
covered with wartlike elevations.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Warty-back</ent>⟦br⟧
